        geekModeText: "While isolated compounds like Astragaloside IV and Cycloastragenol have specific targets, the whole Astragalus root provides a synergistic matrix of saponins, flavonoids (like calycosin and formononetin), and polysaccharides (APS). The whole root extract exerts a broader \"tonic\" effect. The flavonoids are potent antioxidants that scavenge ROS and improve endothelial function. The polysaccharides are the primary immunomodulators, enhancing the activity of B-cells and T-cells. The synergy allows for simultaneous support of immune surveillance, metabolic regulation (via PPAR-gamma modulation), and kidney protection (anti-fibrotic). This holistic action supports the \"Integrative Hallmarks\" of aging, particularly Altered Intercellular Communication and Stem Cell Exhaustion, by maintaining the microenvironment required for healthy tissue turnover.<sup>33</sup>",
