        detailedDescription: "Taurine is a sulfur-containing amino acid that supports mitochondrial function, calcium handling, and metabolic health. Recent research has elevated its status as a longevity molecule due to the observation that taurine levels decline significantly with age. It impacts Mitochondrial Dysfunction, Genomic Instability, Telomere Attrition, and Cellular Senescence.",
