        geekModeText: "Nicotinamide Riboside (NR) is a nucleoside precursor to NAD+. Unlike Nicotinamide (NAM), NR utilizes specific kinases (NRK1/2) to bypass the rate-limiting enzyme NAMPT in the NAD+ salvage pathway. This allows for rapid replenishment of intracellular NAD+ pools, which decline with age. Elevated NAD+ activates Sirtuins (SIRT1/3), which deacetylate mitochondrial proteins (like SOD2 and IDH2), enhancing oxidative phosphorylation efficiency and antioxidant defense (Mitochondrial Dysfunction).<sup>159</sup>  \nNR also supports PARP activity, essential for DNA repair (Genomic Instability). In stem cells, NR restores mitochondrial function and prevents senescence, rejuvenating muscle and neural stem cell populations (Stem Cell Exhaustion). NR has been shown to reduce neuroinflammation and improve cognitive function in Alzheimer's models by normalizing the NAD+/NADH ratio and reducing Aβ toxicity. It effectively re-energizes the cell's metabolic machinery.<sup>161</sup>",
